.TH "pci_rebar_get_current_size" 9 "pci_rebar_get_current_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_rebar_get_current_size \- get the current size of a BAR
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_rebar_get_current_size
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "int bar "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
PCI device
.IP "bar" 12
BAR to set size to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read the size of a BAR from the resizable BAR config.
Returns size if found or negative error code.
